properties.property:
Hi, and welcome to the P.I. Training Camp. We will be conducting your instruction here. Now move, fast! fast!
Use [WASD] to move around.
Follow the yellow arrow (Use [W]) to the next area, a colleague is waiting for you.
If you need to recall anything, just press [E] when near me or any of my colleagues.

You might have noticed that when pressing [W] does not seem go up, instead it appears to move up-right in the screen.
This is because this game is in isometric perspective. [W] does indeed go North, but North from this point of view is in the top-right corner of your screen.
In short: * [W] is North and moves top-right. * [S] is South and moves down-left. * [A] is West and moves top-left. * [D] is East and moves bottom-right.
It might take a bit of time to get used to. Walk around in this room for a bit. When you feel confortable, follow the yellow arrow.
If you need to recall any of this, press [E] near any of us to see these messages repeated.

Hope you had no problem moving around.
The next section is quite dark, but you'll notice that your vision adapts to darkness. When we see in the dark we tend to see bluish hues, but beware, this works up to certain point. If the place is too dark, it will appear pitch black.
Vision adaptation requires time, which means that moving too fast might make areas appear pitch black for a while or burning white when suddenly moving to a bright area.
Follow the yellow line and notice how over time the dark areas will brighten, also becoming bluish.
Beware of the darkness! Being in the dark with a ghost turns people insane.
Follow the yellow line and talk to my colleague for your next instructions.

You can't always count on your vision to look on dark places, you should always have a flashlight with you.
The flashlight should be on your left hand (Bottom left corner of the screen). You can activate any item you put in there with the [TAB] key.
Try to press [TAB] to turn on the flashlight. (After closing this dialog)
The flashlight has 4 modes: OFF, LOW, MID, HI. These are different power levels. The flashlight can overheat so prefer to use the LOW setting where possible.
From now on, there will be very little light, try to have your flashlight always ON so you can see where you are going.
(Remember you can re-open this dialog by pressing [E] near me)

Enough with the baby sitting! My comrades have been too nice. Let's get serious for once.
Behind me there is a door. Your task is to open it and go through.
To open and close doors you must use [E] near them.
On my right there are two glass pannels. We've been using these to contain ghosts lately. But we have no ghosts for you in this facility, rest easy. That would be in a different training location after you finish here.
For now, keep following the yellow lines and open the doors.

Switches! Those that you see on the wall, you toggle them and boom! a light turns on! or, off who knows... the mystery of the switches is fascinating, isn't it?
You can see that in this room we have two switches for lights, they're on the wall on the top-left and top-right of this room.
Use [E] to toggle them.
You'll see they're linked together. As they're for the same room, they control the same lights.
The lights are on the ceiling, so you cannot see them from the isometric perspective; they're effectively invisible.
However, on the next room you'll see a lamp. Try clicking [E] on the lamp and you'll see that triggers only that, not the room lights.

Here we have a sample of our ghost containment unit; you will see these later where you can safely watch a ghost from a distance.
I want to bring your attention to the light switch on my right, just next to the door.
Do you notice how the shape of that switch is a bit different? These are called "external switches". These will actuate the lights of the room behind them.
Regular switches as those you can see on the perimeter of this floor actuate the lights of the very same room they're in.
External switches actuate the lights of the room you're about to enter instead.
Also, this containment room also has a small lamp, you can also actuate it with [E].
You might also notice that this room has ceiling lamps that are visible. This is because these lamps are attached to the wall, not to the ceiling. In fact, they're wall lamps, not ceiling lamps.
Play around with the lights here until you grasp the idea. Once you grasp it, please continue the circuit as usual by following the yellow arrows.

Welcome to the most fun part of this training exercise: The Lab.
A Laboratory you say? no, no.. We call it "The Lab" because it's a maze, a Lab-erynth.
No yellow arrows in this section. Best of luck. Try to find the exit to the next training area.
Remember to use [TAB] to use your Flashlight. [E] to trigger light switches and to open doors.
My colleague will be waiting on the other side. Have fun!

Congratulations, you made it out of The Lab!
In the next room, check our in-development advanced technological device: The Main Breaker.
This device will be capable of shutting off all the electricity in the location.
It is red when electricity is cut, green if there is electricity in the location. You can use [E] to toggle.
Unfortunately this is still a test model and it does nothing aside from changing colors.

Hey recruit, the last part was a bit empty,we're still working on that.
Here, have a look on your new transport vehicle, the BUSTER-MKZERO.
It contains all sorts of useful stuff, such as EMF monitoring (broken), Sensor reading (broken) and much more!
For now all the MKZERO version can do is to carry your gear, and craft a Ghost repellant that will help you expelling ghosts from the location.
Now, just to give you an idea of what a ghost is, we have a live containment unit ahead. Interesting, isn't it?
Oh, they told you that we did not have ghosts here? Oh well, this one is a recent adquisition. It just arrived a few hours ago.
General Kent will explain you more details.

Behind me is the Ghost Containment Unit.
Please note carefully two things:
1) The ghost looks like a floating mist. 2) There is a glowing dust in the middle of the room, this is the ghost's breach.
These are mostly transparent so they can be easy to miss.
The breach is the link between our dimension and the ghost's dimension. It is what allows the ghost to be here, and the ghost is drawn towards it.
Please DO NOT enter the ghost containment unit. If you do, you are at your OWN RISK.
Follow the yellow arrows and proceed to the final briefing area.

Here's your new BUSTER-MKZERO, hope you take good care of it.
You can enter it by pressing [E] near the green mark.
Once inside, you can get out either by pressing [ESC] or clicking the green "Exit Truck" button.
It has two main pages, displayed as tabs in the top:
- Loadout - Journal
Loadout is where you can grab which items you want to use in your investigation. Make sure to select which ones you want, as you'll not be finding anything useful empty handed.
Journal is where you note down your findings and try to guess which ghost it is. Once you get the ghost, you select it, and the "Create Repellent" green button will enable. That will allow you to expel the ghost. But more on that another time.
For now, take a look to the vehicle and press "End Mission" once you're good.
This is the end of the Basic Tutorial.
